<HEAD>Wife Of Guerrilla Acquitted In Kidnapping</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge acquitted the wife of a former
IRA guerrilla of charges she took part in the kidnapping of a
wealthy Dublin dentist.
   Judge Liam Hamilton of the anti-terrorist Special Criminal Court
on Thursday cleared Clare O'Hare, 27, of a charge of falsely
imprisoning 38-year-old dentist John O'Grady.
   He said the prosecution had not proven that Mrs. O'Hare, who is
seven months pregnant, knew of the kidnapping.
   Dessie O'Hare, 29, was sentenced last month to 40 years in
prison on charges of falsely imprisoning the dentist and
maliciously wounding him.
   Police said a five-man gang led by O'Hare chopped off the tips
of two of O'Grady's fingers during the dentist's 22 days in
captivity.
   O'Grady was freed by police in a Dublin house on Nov. 5.
   O'Hare is a former member of the Irish Republican Army and Irish
National Liberation Army, which are fighting to rid
Protestant-dominated Northern Ireland of British rule.
