<2ND_LINE>PM-People-Bing,0360</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lady Bing Arrested for Violating Court Order</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The wife of former Metropolitan Opera director
Sir Rudolf Bing was again ordered to leave her husband alone for
six hours a day and to stay away from the woman she is accused of
slapping.
   Carroll Douglass Bing, 48, was arrested Thursday at the Essex
House apartment on exclusive Central Park South she shares with
Bing, 86.
   She was arrested because she violated a court order that she
stay away from her husband so nurses can take care of him, police
said. Bing suffers from Alzheimer's disease. Lady Bing is a former
mental patient.
   Due to her arrest, Lady Bing missed a court appearance to answer
a charge that on Feb. 24 she slapped Barbara Quinones, vice
president of Columbia Artists Management Inc.
   The judge in that case, Paula Omansky, issued a bench warrant
for Lady Bing's arrest. She was brought before Omansky, who vacated
the bench warrant and adjourned the charge in contemplation of
dismissal.
   During the proceeding Lady Bing walked around, talking and
running her hands through her straw-colored hair. A court officer
ordered her to sit.
   ``You don't understand,'' Lady Bing said. ``I have to go home.
I've been all day without food _ zero food, drink, nothing, not
even one french fry.''
   Omansky renewed an order for Lady Bing ``to stay away from Mrs.
Quinones and not harass her.''
   Later, the district attorney's office said it wouldn't prosecute
Lady Bing for violating Monday's order by state Supreme Court
Justice Carmen Ciparick to leave her husband alone for six hours a
day so that a nurse can feed and cleanse him.
   ``We're going to decline to prosecute this as a criminal
matter,'' spokeswoman Colleen Roche said.
   Lady Bing is in a civil court fight with her husband's lawyer,
Paul Goldhamer, who has asked Ciparick to annul the Bings' marriage.
   Goldhamer, who charges that Lady Bing has abused her husband
verbally and physically, says Bing did not know what he was doing
when he got married in Arlington, Va. on Jan. 9, 1987.
</TEXT>
