<HEAD>Second Man Dies After Bank Bombing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A second man has died as a result of the
bombing of Citibank's India headquarters in downtown New Delhi, a
hospital official said Friday.
   Meher Chand, 55, a retired Indian government employee, died of
his injuries Thursday at Ram Manohar Hospital, said the official,
who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   Another man died and at least 14 people were injured when a bomb
exploded Tuesday at the Citibank offices on the third floor of a
12-story building. All the victims were Indians. Citibank is based
in New York.
   Two of the victims were reported in critical condition.
   No one claimed responsiblity for the blast. Police said the bomb
was concealed in a briefcase.
   The U.S. Embassy in New Delhi issued an advisory telling
employees of American companies ``to take security precautions.''
 
