<1ST_LINE>r i AM-SwissAuction     05-13 0180</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Swiss Auction,0185</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Aga Khan Jewels Sold; Record For Napoleon Pearl</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GENEVA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Kuwaiti banker paid a record $864,000 for a
single pearl that Napoleon gave to his wife, and jewels of the late
Moslem spiritual leader Aga Khan III sold for $3 million at auction.
   Katharina Feller, a spokeswoman for Christie's auction house,
said the price paid for the Regente pearl Thursday night was more
than double the previous record for a single pearl.
   Napoleon had the pearl set in the center of a tiara for Empress
Marie Louise, his second wife.
   Ms. Feller said the buyer, who did not want to be named, bought
the piece as a birthday present for his sister.
   The Aga Khan collection included a 33-carat pear-shaped diamond.
It fetched about $1.8 million, nearly twice its estimated value. A
brooch and diamond bracelet, both including emeralds with Koran
inscriptions, went for almost $1 million.
   The buyers remained anonymous.
   Of wealthy Iranian descent, the Aga Khan died in 1957 and was
succeeded by his grandson as leader of the Ismaili Moslem faith.
</TEXT>
