<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Young Driver,0106</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Seven-Year-Old Caught After Chase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 7-year-old boy driving a
stolen car led police on a chase at speeds up to 93 mph before
being forced off a highway and apprehended, state radio reported
Friday.
   The South African Broadcasting Corp. said the boy, who was not
identified, apparently stole the car in the town of Carletonville,
about 30 miles west of Johannesburg. He was caught on a highway
near Soweto, Johannesburg's black satellite city.
   The report said the chase Wednesday began when a traffic officer
spotted what appeared to be a driverless car speeding along the
road.
</TEXT>
