<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Niger-Ambassador     05-13 0133</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Niger-Ambassador,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Niger Names Ambassador To United States and U.N.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NIAMEY, Niger (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Col. Moumouni Djermakoye has been named
ambassador to the United States from this west African nation.
   Djermakoye, a member of the supreme military council that has
ruled Niger since 1974, will also serve as ambassador to the United
Nations.
   He is considered to be among the most politically influential
men in his country, having served as Niger's foreign minister,
minister of social affairs, minister of health, and prefect in the
department of Zinder in southern Niger.
   Djermakoy was one of the leading contenders to succeed the late
Nigerien president Seyni Kountche, who died in a Paris hospital
last November.
   Kountche was replaced by his former military chief of staff, Ali
Seibou, who was appointed by the military council.
</TEXT>
