<2ND_LINE>PM-Reagan-Iceland,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Prime Minister's trip Delayed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A visit to Washington by Prime Minister
Thorsteinn Palsson of Iceland that had been scheduled for next week
has been postponed because of political developments in his
country, the White House announced today.
   The postponement was disclosed in a one-paragraph announcement
issued less than two hours after White House spokesman Marlin
Fitzwater had listed the event as among the visits on the
president's schedule. Reagan and Palsson were to meet Monday.
   ``Due to internal political developments, the government of
Iceland has requested a postponement of the official working visit
of Prime Minister Palsson, scheduled to begin May 16,'' the
announcement said. ``We share the disappointment that the visit
will not take place at this time.''
