<2ND_LINE>PM-Plant Explosion,0141</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Dead, At Least Two Hurt in Explosion at Chemical Plant</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILLOW ISLAND, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion and fire ripped through
a production unit at a chemical plant today, killing one person and
injuring at least two, authorities said.
   The blast occurred in a building at the American Cyanamid plant
at Willow Island, Pleasants County sheriff's officials said.
   One man was killed and two or three people were injured in the
11:15 a.m. explosion, said Vane Deem of the Belmont Volunteer Fire
Department.
   The fire was contained by shortly after noon, according to the
sheriff's department.
   A department spokeswoman said she did not know what material had
exploded.
   ``They make all kinds of things down there. I'm not sure what
was involved,'' said the woman, who would not give her name.
</TEXT>
