<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--MoslemDemonstration     05-13 0149</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Moslem Demonstration,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Demonstrators March For Khomenini, Against Israel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Moslem demonstrators chanting against Israel
and for a Palestinian homeland paraded past the White House and
through the center of Washington Friday.
   More than 1,000 men, women and children were in the throng,
carrying large banners, some with photographs of the Ayatollah
Ruhollah Khomeini, the Iranian revolutionary leader.
   The demonstration occurred on the last Friday of the Islamic
holy month of Ramadan. Various Palestinian, Pakistani, Iranian and
other groups, including students, took part.
   Participants with portable loudspeakers led the orderly paraders
in chants such as ``Cancer of the Middle East, Israel must not
exist,'' ``Israel is the hate state,'' ``Superpowers are the same.
Down with all of them,'' ``Zionism is terrorism'' and ``Stop the
Holy Land holocaust.''
   Some of the banners protested U.S. support of Israel and
denounced Israel and South Africa as ``twin racist regimes.''
</TEXT>
