<1ST_LINE>r i AM--HongKong-Immigrants     05-13 0161</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM--Hong Kong-Immigrants,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Illegal Immigrants From China Given Jail Terms</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Hong Kong magistrate sentenced 67 illegal
immigrants from China to jail Friday under a new government policy
to prosecute such offenders before returning them to China.
   Sixty-six of the defendants entered this British colony
illegally for the first time and received jail terms of 15 months.
The remaining defendant, who was caught for the second time, was
sentenced to 18 months. They are to be returned to China after
serving the time.
   The illegal immigrants pleaded guilty to the charge of staying
illegally in Hong Kong. Maximum penalty for the offense is a fine
of $625 and three years imprisonment.
   The government introduced the new policy in an attempt to stem
the flow of such illegal immigrants. Previously, illegal immigrants
were immediately repatriated.
   According to police figures, 2,704 illegal Chinese immigrants
entered Hong Kong in April, compared to 1,694 in the same month
last year.
</TEXT>
