<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Whitney Houston, Phil Collins, Miriam Makeba, Dire
Straits and the Eurythmics are among the musicians who will mark
jailed black South African leader Nelson Mandela's 70th birthday
with a 10-hour rock extravaganza.
   The Anti-Apartheid Movement said the June 11 concert will be the
high point of five months of birthday celebrations and rallies for
Mandela. Proceeds will go to the AAM and South African charities.
   The movement said the concert lineup also includes Simple Minds,
the Bees Gees, the Fat Boys, Hugh Masekela, Ashford and Simpson,
Joe Cocker, Roberta Flack, Natalie Cole, George Michael and Sade.
