<2ND_LINE>AM-Wortham Sentenced,0208</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Wortham Sentenced to 376 Years for Capitol Hill Rapes</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOE WHEELAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge sentenced a rapist Friday to the longest
prison term ever imposed in Colorado _ 326 years _ and called him a
``savage parasite'' for his sexual assaults on six women in
Denver's Capitol Hill area.
   Quintin Wortham, 28, convicted Monday of 14 counts of sexual
assault, burglary and theft for the attacks in 1985 and 1986, drew
the maximum sentence from Judge Lynne Hufnagel.
   ``The possibility is remote that Quintin Wortham will be
anything but a savage parasite,'' she said.
   The sentence is the longest ever imposed in Colorado, said
District Attorney Norm Early.
   ``It sent a very definite, clear, easy-to-hear and appropriate
message,'' Early said.
   All but the two theft charges against Wortham brought
consecutive sentences.
   After reciting what Hufnagel described as Wortham's ``sordid
record,'' the judge said, ``The record is devoid of any positive
contributions to family or society.''
   Wortham's criminal record dates back to 1972 and included
numerous arrests for burglary and theft, and two earlier counts of
sexual assault. He was on parole at the time of the Capitol Hill
assaults.
