<1ST_LINE>r a AM-MagnumCrash     05-13 0159</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Magnum Crash,0167</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>`Magnum' Stunt Coordinator Injured In Chopper Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The helicopter stunt coordinator for ``Magnum,
P.I.'' was injured Friday when one of the choppers used in the TV
series crashed in a pineapple field during a cargo-hauling flight,
authorities said.
   Steve Kux, 41, was listed in fair condition at Queen's Medical
Center with broken bones and cuts.
   Kux, who did much of aerial work for the CBS series that ended
May 1 after an eight-year run, was hauling equipment for the
Hawaiian Electric Co.
   The Hughes 500-D helicopter, still painted brown with orange and
yellow stripes as it appeared in the series starring Tom Selleck,
apparently experienced electrical problems, said Capt. Elmo Lincoln
of the Waialua Fire Station.
   Two Hawaiian Electric Co. employees pulled Kux from the
wreckage, he said. Lux was the only person aboard.
   Calls to the aircraft's owner, Cherry Helicopters of Honolulu,
were not immediately returned.
   The crash is under investigation.
</TEXT>
