<HEAD>PANAMA:</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   LA NEGRITA, Panama _ The de facto leader of Panama, Gen. Manuel
Antonio Noriega, says ``everything fell apart'' in talks with the
United States about his leaving power. White House spokesman
insists, ``We are still negotiating.'' U.S. drug charges against
Noriega might be dropped if he steps down. PM-Panama.
