<1ST_LINE>u a AM-CollegeFrat     05-13 0319</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-College Frat,0329</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>College Council Recommends Fraternity Be Suspended For Sexist
Incident</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DANICA KIRKA</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MONTPELIER, Vt. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Middlebury College council Friday
recommended a year's suspension for a fraternity that hung a
mutilated, bloodied female mannequin from a balcony during a toga
party.
   The council, made up of students, faculty members and staff,
deliberated four hours before reaching the decision.
   The recommendation goes to college President Olin Robison, who
has the final say on the fate of Delta Upsilon, which dangled the
mannequin from its fraternity house last weekend.
   The council recommended the fraternity be banned and its members
prohibited from living in the house for a year, after which the
council would decide whether to close the fraternity, suspend it
another year or allow its return on probation.
   The council also recommended that fraternity members and others
at the 1,950-student liberal arts college participate in a
sexism-awareness program, said college spokesman Ron Nief.
   ``I'm definitely pleased that some sort of awareness program
(will begin),'' said Jennifer Weiss, a student who wrote a letter
of complaint about the incident. ``I think that the point I was
interested in making was brought to light. Hopefully, the awareness
will continue.''
   The president of Delta Upsilon at Middlebury said that the
punishment was too stiff and that publicity about the incident
influenced the council's decision.
   ``I felt in some ways we were guilty before we were even
tried,'' said Mark Lahive. ``It was not aimed to be a public
display against women at all. ... There was no harm intended. ...
It wasn't a statement at all.''
   Lahive said the fraternity would ask its alumni to lobby on the
group's behalf.
   Weiss and six other students wrote a letter to Robison that said
the mannequin was hung with a rope around its neck, its head bashed
in and its breasts dripping with what looked like blood.
</TEXT>
