<DATELINE>CULVER CITY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Investor Marvin Davis has renewed his
bid for ailing television producer Lorimar Telepictures Inc., just
two days after Lorimar agreed to become part of Warner
Communications Inc.
   Davis, who previously offered $17 per share for the maker of
such hit TV series as ``Dallas'' and ``Knots Landing,'' notified
the company Thursday that he would pay $15 cash per share, or
$679.5 million.
   Lorimar values the tentative stock swap agreement it made with
Warner Tuesday at $1.18 billion, including assumption of $550
million in Lorimar debt.
</TEXT>
