   The stock market struggled to a small gain Thursday in a bid to
rebound from Wednesday's broad decline. The Dow Jones average of 30
industrials, down 37.80 on Wednesday, recovered 2.15 points to
1,968.00.
   The dollar finished slightly lower while gold prices rose.
   Bond prices fell.
   A five-day rally that pushed soybean futures prices to four-year
highs ended as rainy weather forecasts persuaded traders to take
profits.
