<1ST_LINE>r f PM-OilPrices     05-13 0168</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Oil Prices,0176</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Oil Prices Edge Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oil prices have slipped lower in listless
trading.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange Thursday, June contracts for
West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark U.S. crude grade, closed at
$17.48 per barrel, down 1 cent from Wednesday's close.
   Among refined products for June delivery, contracts for
wholesale unleaded gasoline fell 0.33 cent to 51.92 cents per
gallon, while wholesale heating oil dropped 0.23 cent to 47.23
cents per gallon.
   John H. O'Connell, an analyst at the Refco Inc. commodities
trading firm, said trading was slow due to a lack of market-moving
news.
   ``It got a good-sized runup yesterday, and gave some of that
back today,'' he said.
   O'Connell was referring mainly to the June unleaded gasoline
contract, which rose 0.63 cent per gallon Wednesday after a report
by the American Petroleum Institute showed heavy stock drawdowns
last week.
   Shrinkages in inventories and production encouraged traders to
buy in anticipation that shorter supplies might lead to higher
prices.
</TEXT>
