<HEAD>Soybean Futures Skyrocket On Dry Weather Outlook</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soybean futures prices skyrocketed Friday and
grain futures also closed higher after the National Weather Service
predicted a month of drier-than-normal growing conditions.
   Soybean futures, which have risen sharply during the past week,
leaped as much as 14{ cents a bushel and set new contract highs
across the board.
   Large speculative firms such as Refco Inc. and C&D Commodities
led the trade, analysts said.
   The National Weather Service said in its 30-day outlook that the
Ohio River valley, central Mississippi River valley and the
