<1ST_LINE>r f AM-FederatedLayoffs     05-13 0265</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Federated Layoffs,0274</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>92 Federated Employees Lose Jobs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ninety-two employees at the Federated
Department Stores Inc. corporate offices in Cincinnati were laid
off Friday as part of the retailer's acquisition by Campeau Corp.
of Canada.
   Federated spokeswoman Carol Sanger said the layoffs range from
senior management to clerical staff.
   She said many workers were relieved that the layoffs weren't
more extensive at the headquarters, which has 530 workers in
downtown and regional offices.
   ``Pretty much all departments are going to be affected,'' she
said. ``What is happening is a restructuring of the integrated
organization. The key is that all department functions are going to
be maintained, which again is a much better position than we had
originally anticipated.''
   Campeau officials have said repeatedly that some Federated
workers would lose their jobs at the corporate headquarters as part
of the acquisition.
   ``It's been no secret from the outset that there would be
cutbacks, and people are ready to get on with their lives and
probably will feel some relief today that their futures are
defined,'' Ms. Sanger said.
   She said those who lost their jobs Friday will receive severance
packages ranging from at least 13 weeks of pay to as many as 20
weeks. The company also will help employees with job placement
counseling.
   Federated was acquired by Toronto-based Campeau following a
two-month takeover battle. Control of Cincinnati-based Federated
passed to Campeau last week when the developer announced it had
accepted more than 87 million shares tendered by the retailer's
stockholders. The merger is expected to be completed in about a
month.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
